OL,3,CArchbishop welcomes new Bishop of
OL,4,CDerry Michael Router
OL,6,FBishop Michael Router has been
OL,7,Fannounced as the Catholic Church's new
OL,8,FBishop of Derry after Pope Leo
OL,9,Faccepted the retirement of Donal
OL,10,FMcKeown from the diocese.
OL,12,FArchbishop Eamon Martin welcomed the
OL,13,Fappointment of his former assistant
OL,14,Fsaying, "he has been a tremendous
OL,15,Fsupport to me as Auxiliary Bishop of
OL,16,FArmagh...we will miss him a lot".
OL,18,FHe also said Bishop Router's "warm
OL,19,Fpersonality and leadership skills"
OL,20,Fwould be an asset in his new role.
OL,1,W~k4 jw=hw1 hw}h7}j7}            G1/7
OL,2,W/*% /*%/"-$+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
